(1) A Council shall keep or cause to be kept books of account of all income and expenditure and proper records in relation to its accounts.
A Council shall keep or cause to be kept books of account of all income and expenditure and proper records in relation to its accounts.
(2) A Council shall cause to be prepared not later than three months after the end of each financial year- (a) a statement of income and expenditure during the financial year; (b) a statement of assets and liabilities of the university on the last day of financial year; (c) a report on the progress of the university during the financial year; and shall submit such statements and reports to the Government and to such other bodies as the Council may determine.
